The paid‐in capital is recorded as an injection made at inception, and none of the subsequent transactions (purchases, expenses, etc.) affect this account. In our data, the only transactions that increase paid‐in capital are the three beginning ones made on 2023‑12‑31:

• Cash deposit: 3,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit: 5,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets: 5,000,000.0  

Summing these gives: 3,000,000.0 + 5,000,000.0 + 5,000,000.0 = 13,000,000.0

Since no additional paid‐in capital transactions occur during the period, the “Paid-in Capital End Value” remains the same as the initial injection.

Thus, the answer is:

{"solution": {"Paid-in Capital Initial Value": "13000000.00", "Paid-in Capital End Value": "13000000.00"}}
